$section Running the Cppad Py Tests$$

$children%setup.py
	%bin/get_cppad.sh
%$$

$head Configuration$$
You must edit $cref setup.py$$
to configure Cppad Py for your system.

$head get_cppad.sh$$
The next step is to get a copy of Cppad using the command
$pre
	$$$cref%bin/get_cppad.sh%get_cppad.sh%$$

$head setup.py$$
The next step is the build the Python cppad_py module using
one of the command:
$codei%
	%python% setup.py build_ext --inplace
%$$
where $icode python$$ is the Python executable you will be
using with Cppad Py.

$head check$$

$subhead python$$
The next step is to check the cppad_py python interface
$cref py_lib$$ on your system using
$codei%
	cd lib/example/python
	%python% check_all.py
%$$

$head c++$$
You can check the cppad_py c++ interface
$cref cpp_lib$$ on your system using
$codei%
	cd build
	make check_lib_cplusplus
%$$

$end
